column1: #Text=T. Narsipur or Tirumakudal Narsipur is a temple town in Mysore district of Karnataka province in India .
#Text=Narsipur is at the confluence of three holy rivers and so has many temples of ancient origin .
#Text=Narsipur is 132 km from Bangalore and 35 km from Mysore .
#Text=Road is the only option available as there are no railway stations or airports .
#Text=The nearest operating airport is at Bangalore .
#Text=Autorikshaws are the best option for getting around .
#Text=Avoid local buses as they stop everywhere and take a lot of time .
#Text=Vidyodaya College and Ganapathi temple areas near the bus station are good for a peaceful walk .
#Text=The temple at Sosale village is only at a distance of three kilometers and the temple premises are ideal for a picnic as there absolute silence and a vast expanse of paddy fields surround you .
#Text=The temple is not visited by many but it is breathtakingly beautiful .
#Text=A trip to Mysore via Bannur town is very refreshing because of many green villages and temples on the way .
#Text=After T. Narsipur , the road to Bannur goes through Sosale , Somanathpur and Kethupura before reaching Bannur town .
#Text=After Bannur , there are villages like Madegowdahuddi , Hunganahalli , Bidarahalli , Harohalli and Mellahally .
#Text=After Harohalli , the trip becomes a little suburban with engineering colleges and residential suburbs beginning to appear .
#Text=After the police checkpost at Delhi Public School area , the ring road appears .
#Text=There is a resort called Vilasi which is going to open in 2016 and the ring road junction marks the beginning of the city .
#Text=The next junction is called Teresian college junction which is well inside Mysore city .
#Text=High class shopping is possible only in Mysore city .
#Text=T. Narsipur has a fairly big market offering wares for the village people .
#Text=Beware of food items as they can be of unhealthy type .
#Text=But jackfruits and pineapples you can try as they are offered in small pieces wrapped in clean plastic packets .
#Text=Srinivasa Restaurant , opp . Bus Station , T. Narsipur .
#Text=Good place for clean vegetarian food like chapathis , rice and vegetable preparations .
#Text=Udupi Hotel , Near Taluk office , T. Narsipur .
#Text=Home made food , first hotel of T. Narasipur , Good place for clean and hygeinic vegetarian food like Dosa , Idli , Puliyogare , Jamun , etc
#Text=There are many small and economical lodges in T. Narasipur .
#Text=Most of them have only basic facilities meant for temple visitors .
